Coos,

June, 1895. Jordan v. Atherton & Tr. Thomas F. Johnson and Drew, Jordan & Buckley, for the plaintiff. Jason H. Dudley and George H. Bingham, for the defendant.

Foreign Attachment. The question reserved was “how much the trustee should be charged.” The amount was adjudged to be $400.

Clark, J., did not sit: the others concurred.
